riend. I’d work for him as a gardener, and then afterwards his garden would become mine, and I’d always remember my dead comrade with grateful tears. We’d fiddle together, or, say, he’d play the flute and I the mandolin. But women … now, really, could you name a single one who did not deceive her husband?”

“All very true! Very true indeed. It’s a pleasure to hear you talk. Did you ever go to school?”

